page.title: 15LANDCOVER
page.content: The primary land-cover in our area is grassland and farmland. Much of the land in this area is farmland owned by a group of people, but tenanted out to farmers. The secondry land-cover in our area are woods. Most of the trees are around Hazlegrove House School, in Yarcombe Wood and Forty Acre Copse, but there are also many other trees. The tertiary land-cover here are buildings. These are very scattered except for in Babcary and at Hazlegrove, although the amount of land covered by buildings are far behind grassland. Babcary is quite a small village and the main factor why there are no new houses is the fact that there is no mains drainage,and the villlage will not really start to expand until there is mains drainage available.
